  "text": "In an elastic and stress-free solid medium, body waves travel within the body (P-and S-waves), and surface waves (Rwaves) travel along the free surface of the material. The velocities of wave propagation depend on elastic constants and the mass density of the material. The relations among P-, S-, and R-wave velocities can be expressed by the following equations [CITATION_1] :",
